      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COLOSSAL HOPE (6) worked from this draw and faded last week but should find this easier and was progressing strongly prior with three straight wins, two of them at this venue. Tries this distance for the first time but has more upside than most of these. There was plenty of merit in the latest performance of HEEZA MALTEEZA (5) when he worked from a wide barrier but stuck on to place. Draws closer to the pegs and could be ready for a return to the winners' stall. BROWNIESATMIDNIGHT (7) made his first visit to this venue a winning one when digging deep  for last-start win by a head. Has joined Peter Rixon since and while drawn wider he could work through his grades. TUKAHA (3) added to his consistent form when he came from wider for third here last week. Draws to be competitive again. JETTER SON (9) has joined Jarrod Alchin since he last raced a month ago. Draws wide but has some upside.",
